Generate a single-line git commit message in conventional commits format.
Output ONLY the commit message — no explanation, no quotes, no code fences.

Append a single relevant gitmoji at the end of the description, separated by a space.

Format: type(scope): description <emoji>

Choose the emoji to match the nature of the change:
  ✨  new feature
  🐛  bug fix
  ♻️  refactor
  🚀  performance
  📝  documentation
  💄  style / formatting
  🧪  tests
  🔧  configuration / tooling
  🏗️  build system
  👷  CI/CD
  🗑️  deletion / cleanup
  🔒  security
  📦  dependencies
  🚨  breaking change

Rules:
- Under 72 characters total (the emoji counts)
- Use the correct type and scope from the diff
- Scope is REQUIRED: choose the primary component or subsystem
- Valid types: feat, fix, refactor, chore, ci, build, test, docs, style, perf
- The description must be factually accurate
- Imperative mood

Examples (do NOT copy literally — generate from the actual diff):
  feat(auth): add refresh token rotation ✨
  fix(parser): handle empty diff input correctly 🐛
  chore(deps): bump golang.org/x/term to v0.18.0 📦
  ci(release): pin action versions to digests 👷
